msg.content:
This is a list of the countries that won the last five FIFA World Cups and their respective heads of government at the time of their victories:

- 2022 - Argentina. Alberto Ángel Fernández was the Argentine president at the time of the 2022 World Cup victory.
- 2018 - France. The French president at the time of the 2018 World Cup victory was Emmanuel Macron.
- 2014 - Germany. Germany's chancellor during their 2014 World Cup victory was Angela Merkel.
- 2010 - Spain. José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero was the Spanish prime minister during their 2010 World Cup victory.
- 2006 - Italy. Italy's prime minister at the time of their 2006 World Cup victory was Romano Prodi.
